data.title: YES Network
data.meta_description: Comprehensive coverage of the New York Yankees, Brooklyn Nets and New York Liberty including live games, highlights, statistics, rosters, schedules, news and video clips.
data.text:
Aaron Judge became the fastest player to 300 career home runs in the Yankees' 10-2 win over the White Sox. A red-hot Juan Soto hit his fourth homer in two games and Austin Wells added a blast in the historic win.

Box Score

The 76th Yankees Old Timers' Day will take place on Saturday, August 24 at Yankee Stadium. The event will commemorate the 2009 World Series championship team as 17 members of that team will be on hand.

More

Aaron Judge talks about becoming the fastest player to hit 300 career home runs and his inspiration at the plate for the milestone at-bat.

Juan Soto discusses his first career three-home run game after the Yankees' 4-1 win over the White Sox on Tuesday night.

New York City FC’s road to the MLS Cup final ended as they went down against the Union, 3-1, on Sunday night. Maxi Moralez scored the team’s lone goal in the 57th minute.

Box Score

New York City FC took down CF Montréal, 3-1, on Sunday afternoon and advanced to the Eastern Conference Finals. Héber, Maxi Moralez and Talles Magno each netted a goal in the victory.

Box Score

New York City FC defeated Inter Miami, 3-0, on a rainy Monday night to advance to the Eastern Conference semifinals. Gabriel Pereira, Héber and Maxi Moralez each netted goals in the victory.
